search:Angular Internationalization Best.content:
- Use `ng xi18n` to extract i18n messages from your Angular project.
- Update the `angular.json` file with the following configuration:
  ```json
  "i18n": {
    "locales": {
      "fr": "./src/locale/messages.fr.xlf",
      "es": "./src/locale/messages.es.xlf"
    },
    "defaultLocale": "en"
  }
  ```
- Use `ng serve --configuration=fr` to serve your application in French.
- Update the `angular.json` file with the following configuration for multiple locales:
  ```json
  "configurations": {
    "fr": {
      "fileReplacements": [
        {
          "replace": "src/environments/environment.ts",
          "with": "src/environments/environment.fr.ts"
        }
      ],
      "i18nLocale": "fr",
      "i18nFile": "src/locale/messages.fr.xlf"
    },
    "es": {
      "fileReplacements": [
        {
          "replace": "src/environments/environment.ts",
          "with": "src/environments/environment.es.ts"
        }
      ],
      "i18nLocale": "es",
      "i18nFile": "src/locale/messages.es.xlf"
    }
  }
  ```
- Use `ng build --configuration=fr` to build your application in French.
- Update the `angular.json` file with the following configuration for production:
  ```json
  "production": {
    "fileReplacements": [
      {
        "replace": "src/environments/environment.ts",
        "with": "src/environments/environment.prod.ts"
      }
    ],
    "i18nLocale": "fr",
    "i18nFile": "src/locale/messages.fr.xlf"
  }
  ```
- Use `ng build --prod --configuration=fr` to build your production application in French.
- Update the `angular.json` file with the following configuration for testing:
  ```json
  "test": {
    "fileReplacements": [
      {
        "replace": "src/environments/environment.ts",
        "with": "src/environments/environment.test.ts"
      }
    ],
    "i18nLocale": "fr",
    "i18nFile": "src/locale/messages.fr.xlf"
  }
  ```
- Use `ng test --configuration=fr` to run your tests in French.
